Therefore, if Heseltine was to be beaten, it had to be by someone else. President Bush lost an irreplaceable pin supporting his mission in the Persian Gulf on Thanksgiving Day. He heard the news of Margaret Thatcher's resignation as he celebrated the holiday in the Saudi desert -- and it clearly came as a shock. In the State Department, too, it came as a shock. Americans who had come to take Thatcher for granted during her 11 years of power were not prepared for her passing. The feeling everywhere was that Thatcher always stuck to her word. 